description: Name of file containing the data (original  name when the file is downloaded)
Variable code in the original data
Measure category of the variable (pro, fre, beh)
Domain-general or domain-specific  variable (gen or dom)
Name of domain of variable (e.g., smo, alc)

Type of response scale: ordinal (categorical variable with options that can be ranked), discrete (counts with clear range of possible responses, e.g., days in a month 0-30), open-ended (counts with no clear range), composite measure (sum of scores, proportions)
If ordinal or discrete, the number of options/possible responses
For frequency measures, the number of days the measure enquires about.
For behavioural measures, the format of the task: lotteries, multiple price lists, willingness to pay/sell, allocation, dynamic
For behavioural measures, if it was incentivized or hypothetical
Has value 1 if it is a filter question in the survey
